    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-26T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="768"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/7–2649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-26T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 26, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:45 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2954. Deptel 2536, July 21, re freezing Chinese foreign exchange balances.
                        Dening,<note n="46" xml:id="d768fn46">Maberly E. Dening, British Assistant
                        Under-Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs (Far East).</note> Foreign
                    Office, re paragraph 2 of Deptel under reference, states Foreign Office has not
                    been informed opinion Hong Kong [and] Shanghai bank manager and does not
                    contemplate freezing <pb facs="0813" n="803" xml:id="pg_803"/> Chinese foreign
                    exchange assets at present time. Believes Shanghai British unduly panicky
                    although easy to say this when 10,000 miles away. Will consult Treasury and
                    inform Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
